Computers connected to a wide area network (WAN) is a network that covers a broad area
public networks, such as the telephone system.
They can also be connected through leased lines or satellites.
The largest WAN in existence is the Internet.
Typically, a WAN consists of two or more local-area networks (LANs) as [[Subnetwork]].